<br>
Things NOT to say to the party Vol. 1:<br>
&quot;I'm a little bit rusty for taking a sabbatical for 2 weeks. Where are we?&quot;<br>
<br>
A big round of applause to Dinkel (Cleric), Gravlax (Monk, <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Prezto</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->), Grifter (Rogue, <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Wayfarer</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->), Mirdorr (Bard) and Zukul (corpulent Warrior, <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Albarath</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->)! It was one, if not the smoothest, most enjoyable and damn well <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> fun</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, yes! <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> FUN!</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> grouping sessions in my time in Norrath. Good rapport about group members, constant chatter in between and during spawns, and we all naturally adapted to our respective playing styles. A well balanced, harmonious group.<br>
<br>
The gate room was a real <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> rush</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> .. constant spawns, adds, repops .. there was a particular overpull which saw a little too many goblins coming through the door way leading to the 'King/Throne' room hallway .. fire, flames and inferno's, with the odd Solusek running through just for luck. How we never had a wipeout was a mystery .. we thought that Gravlax had hit FD except it proved to be a little too realistic .. Dinkel, our resident cleric, suffered an LD as we all suffered near heart failure. The battle was finely balanced .. Zukul swinging at anything that moved, and if it didn't, whack it until it does! (Troll logic, for you :P); Grifter emerging from the shadows to BS, and found himself tanking at various points, Mirdorr becoming frantically involved in the melee whilst trying to twist various heal songs etc .. and myself desperately lobbing mezzes around to keep the battle at least <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> sane</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.<br>
<br>
Although unknown to the party at the time (I kept my own council), I was <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> dangerously</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> low on mana the <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> whole</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> fight. When the chanter has to find a corner to med, hit a hotkey to stand/sit then cast 'mezz', hit the stand/sit hotkey, yada yada yada on all 5-10% of available mana .. [shiver].<br>
<br>
Just as it appeared that we would be overwhelmed by the goblin hoard, Dinkel re-connected and saved our asses with some finely-timed heals. An incredible adrenalin rush. Also, some exceptional group interaction because nobody retreated during that battle, and kept to the task at hand, even though most were at a sliver of health (1-1/2 red bars left).<br>
<br>
Toss in constant Gnome Clockwork trains around the entrance stairway and <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> rug</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> area, a sizeable zone population, and all the elements that makes EQ so enjoyable were present. <br>
<br>
Well done guys and gals! Even if I nearly fell asleep at the keyboard on a few occasions <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  Next time, I'll think I'll commission a tailor to make a few Handmade tailored backpacks, if I fail to improve my current (46) ish skill level in tailoring towards the 'Holy Grail'.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Each of us received about 20pp. Considering our level, this was a good haul.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
If you weren't so concerned about weight limitations (Bah! Monks :P) you would have made around 55-60pp when the rest of the party sold up all the loot and split the proceeds at the gyspy merchant by the Druid ring. It was an <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> exceptional</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> haul, and I have never in my Norrath life seen so many FS weapons drop. There were Pages, Words, Gems, Shields, FS weapons etc and good coinage, especially as the spawn time in tandem with the various pulling areas re: <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> rug</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> pit</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> and <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> gate</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> rooms produced a non-stop supply of goblins. Tremendous fun!<br>
<br>
I also gained <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> two</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> levels from 22 to a yellow into 24 <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/happy.gif ALT=":D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  It was all about the group interaction, baby! Sol A is a fabulous dungeon which I was heartily glad was recommended to me (and others judging by the population last night), and I couldn't of wished for a more decent group of people.<br>
<br>
Regards,<br>
Riotgirl [Eliza Dushku Form] Hard Woman Enchanter<br>
